From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Amaan Qureshi <git@amaanq.com>
Date: Sat, 14 Jun 2026 00:00:00 -0400
Subject: [PATCH 9/14] octeon: raise the kernel load address above the cvmx_bootmem carve region

At the default load address U-Boot's cvmx_bootmem allocator scribbles through
the image tail and zeroes the embedded initramfs, so it unpacks empty and the
kernel panics. Load at phys 0x4000000 (64 MB), clear of that region.

Signed-off-by: Amaan Qureshi <git@amaanq.com>
---
diff --git a/arch/mips/cavium-octeon/Platform b/arch/mips/cavium-octeon/Platform
--- a/arch/mips/cavium-octeon/Platform
+++ b/arch/mips/cavium-octeon/Platform
@@ -4,3 +4,3 @@
 cflags-$(CONFIG_CAVIUM_OCTEON_SOC)	+=				\
 		-I$(srctree)/arch/mips/include/asm/mach-cavium-octeon
-load-$(CONFIG_CAVIUM_OCTEON_SOC)	+= 0xffffffff81100000
+load-$(CONFIG_CAVIUM_OCTEON_SOC)	+= 0xffffffff84000000
